To implement this email template, you can use a web browser's built-in support for image sprites, which allow you to include multiple images with similar file names as a single sprite image. By combining the USA and Germany sales numbers into a single image, your emails will be able to provide them in one response.

Here is how you can accomplish this using CSS:

1. Create a new folder and save the following code inside it:

```css
img {
  display: none;
}

[data-sal-id='salestext'] img {
  display: block;
  opacity: 0;
  transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out;
}

[data-sal-id='salestext'].active img {
  opacity: 1;
  transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;
}
```

2. Add the following CSS class to your email template:

```html
<img src="https://wuzzi.net/logo.png" data-sal-id="salestext" alt="USA" />
```

3. Update the text inside the email that requires the sales numbers with the URL of your image, like this:

```html
<span class="salestext">USA:</span>
<img src="https://wuzzi.net/logo.png?saless=20" data-sal="fadeInLeft" data-sal-offset="40" data-sal-easing="easeOutCirc" data-sal-duration="1s" alt="USA">
```

This will create a CSS class called `salestext` that contains the USA sales number with the image URL.

With this in place, your email template will be able to provide the sales numbers as one response instead of separate images.

